Items.description: Daniel Mengden struck out eight, Khris Davis hit his career-best 43rd homer and the last-place Oakland Athletics ended the season with a 5-2 win at Texas on Sunday.
Items.vs: Texas Rangers vs. Oakland Athletics

Items.description: Pete Mackanin ended his tenure as Philadelphia Phillies manager with a win, while Terry Collins left the New York Mets with a loss.
Items.vs: Philadelphia Phillies vs. New York Mets

Items.description: Jose Altuve coasted to his third AL batting title despite going hitless in two at-bats, and the Houston Astros scored four times in the seventh inning to rally from a three-run deficit and beat the Boston Red Sox 4-3 on Sunday.
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Parker Bridwell pitched seven scoreless innings in a duel with James Paxton, Eric Young Jr. hit a three-run homer and the Los Angeles Angels beat the Seattle Mariners 6-2 in their season finale Sunday.
Items.vs: Los Angeles Angels vs. Seattle Mariners

Items.description: Giancarlo Stanton came up short in his quest for 60 home runs, and Adonis Garcia hit a pinch-hit three-run home run to lift the Atlanta Braves over the Miami Marlins 8-5 in the season finale for both teams Sunday.
Items.vs: Miami Marlins vs. Atlanta Braves

Items.description: Bartolo Colon made a final bid to be included in Minnesota's postseason rotation, pitching one-run ball into the seventh inning to lead the Twins to a 5-1 victory over the Detroit Tigers in the regular-season finale Sunday.
Items.vs: Minnesota Twins vs. Detroit Tigers

Items.description: Corey Seager had three hits to break out of a funk and the Los Angeles Dodgers headed into the postseason on a high note, holding off the playoff-bound Colorado Rockies 6-3 in the regular-season finale Sunday.
Items.vs: Colorado Rockies vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Blake Snell struck out a career-high 13 in seven innings Sunday and the Tampa Bay Rays beat the Baltimore Orioles 6-0 in a season wrapup.
Items.vs: Tampa Bay Rays vs. Baltimore Orioles

Items.description: Jay Bruce had a two-run single, Josh Tomlin pitched into the sixth inning and the Cleveland Indians got their AL-best 102nd victory, beating the Chicago White Sox 3-1 on Sunday in their regular-season finale.
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. Chicago White Sox

Items.description: Eric Hosmer, Mike Moustakas, Lorenzo Cain and Alcides Escobar tipped their caps and likely said goodbye to Kansas City's fans, and then the playoff-bound Arizona Diamondbacks ended the regular season with a 14-2 win over the Royals on Sunday.
Items.vs: Kansas City Royals vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Aaron Wilkerson took a perfect game into the sixth inning, Brett Phillips hit a three-run homer and the Milwaukee Brewers closed out their near-miss of a season with a 6-1 victory over the St. Louis Cardinals on Sunday.
Items.vs: St. Louis Cardinals vs. Milwaukee Brewers

Items.description: Anthony Rizzo and Kris Bryant each had a light day of work as the Chicago Cubs prepared for the playoffs by playing much of their roster during a 3-1 loss to Deck McGuire and the Cincinnati Reds in the regular-season finale on Sunday.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Cincinnati Reds

Items.description: Didi Gregorius' 3-run homer tied the score after the Twins chased Luis Severino in the first inning, a pumped-up Aaron Judge hit a two-run shot in his postseason debut and the Yankees were rescued by their bullpen in an 8-4 win in the AL wild-card game.
Items.eventTitle: AL WILD CARD GAME -- NYY ADVANCES TO ALDS
Items.title: AL Wild Card Game
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Minnesota Twins

Items.description: Relief pitcher Archie Bradley hit a stunning two-run triple in the seventh inning, one of four three-baggers by Arizona that sent the Diamondbacks past the Colorado Rockies 11-8 in the National League wild-card game Wednesday night.
Items.eventTitle: NL WILD CARD GAME -- ARI ADVANCES TO NLDS
Items.title: NL Wild Card Game
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Colorado Rockies

Items.description: Jose Altuve hit three home runs in an unprecedented show of power for the diminutive major league batting champion as the Houston Astros roughed up Chris Sale and the Boston Red Sox 8-2 on Thursday in Game 1 of the AL Division Series.
Items.title: ALDS Game 1
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Trevor Bauer chopped slugger Aaron Judge and New York's other big bats down to size, and Jay Bruce drove in three runs as the Cleveland Indians began chasing their first World Series title in 69 years with a 4-0 win over the Yankees on Thursday night.
Items.title: ALDS Game 1
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Carlos Correa homered, doubled and drove in four runs, Jose Altuve got two more hits and the Houston Astros hammered the Boston Red Sox 8-2 Friday to take a commanding 2-0 lead in the AL Division Series.
Items.title: ALDS Game 2
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Boston Red Sox

Items.description: Yan Gomes singled home Austin Jackson from second base with none out in the 13th inning as the Cleveland Indians rallied from five runs down to stun the New York Yankees 9-8 Friday and snatch a 2-0 lead in the AL Division Series.
Items.title: ALDS Game 2
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Kyle Hendricks outpitched Stephen Strasburg, and the Chicago Cubs opened defense of their first World Series title in 108 years by beating the Washington Nationals 3-0 on Friday in Game 1 of their NL Division Series.
Items.title: NLDS Game 1
Items.vs: Washington Nationals vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Justin Turner homered and drove in five runs, Clayton Kershaw won despite giving up four homers and the Los Angeles Dodgers roared to a 9-5 victory over the Arizona Diamondbacks on Friday night in their NL Division Series opener.
Items.title: NLDS Game 1
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: Bryce Harper hit a tying two-run homer in the eighth inning and Ryan Zimmerman tacked on a three-run shot moments later to lift the Washington Nationals to a 6-3 comeback victory over the defending World Series champion Chicago Cubs on Saturday.
Items.title: NLDS Game 2
Items.vs: Washington Nationals vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Yasiel Puig had three hits and drove in two runs, Austin Barnes added a key two-run double and the Los Angeles Dodgers used another relentless offensive performance to beat the Arizona Diamondbacks 8-5 on Saturday night for a 2-0 series lead.
Items.title: NLDS Game 2
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Arizona Diamondbacks

Items.description: David Price pitched four scoreless innings of relief after another Boston starter faltered, and 20-year-old Rafael Devers connected for a key homer as the Red Sox beat the Houston Astros 10-3 on Sunday to stave off elimination in Game 3.
Items.title: ALDS Game 3
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Masahiro Tanaka's seven-inning gem was saved when Aaron Judge prevented a home run in right field, and Greg Bird homered to give the New York Yankees a 1-0 victory over the Cleveland Indians in Game 3 on Sunday night, extending their AL Division Series.
Items.title: ALDS Game 3
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Justin Verlander outpitched Chris Sale in a relief role reversal of aces, and the Houston Astros advanced to their first AL Championship Series, rallying past the Boston Red Sox 5-4 Monday in Game 4 of their playoff matchup.
Items.title: ALDS Game 4
Items.vs: Boston Red Sox vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Anthony Rizzo hit a tiebreaking single with two outs in the eighth inning and the Chicago Cubs overcame Max Scherzer's brilliant performance to beat the Washington Nationals 2-1 on Monday for a 2-1 lead in their NL Division Series.
Items.title: NLDS Game 3
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Luis Severino bounced back from his playoff debacle, slumping Aaron Judge delivered a big hit and the New York Yankees beat the Cleveland Indians 7-3 Monday night to force a Game 5 in their ALDS.
Items.title: ALDS Game 4
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Cleveland Indians

Items.description: Cody Bellinger homered, drove in two runs and flipped over a dugout railing to steal an out for a dominant Yu Darvish, helping the Dodgers beat the Diamondbacks 3-1 Monday night to finish a three-game sweep in their NL Division Series.
Items.title: NLDS Game 3
Items.vs: Arizona Diamondbacks vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: The showers came a little late, but the rain that soaked Wrigley Field and washed out Game 4 of the NL Division Series followed Tuesday's forecast pretty closely.
Items.title: NLDS Game 4.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: Stephen Strasburg shook off an illness and all doubts about his mettle to pitch seven dominant innings, Michael A. Taylor hit a late grand slam and the Washington Nationals beat the Chicago Cubs 5-0 on Wednesday.
Items.title: NLDS Game 4.
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Washington Nationals

Items.description: The Yankees staved off elimination for the fourth time in this postseason, topping the Indians 5-2 in Game 5 of the ALDS to complete their comeback from a 2-0 series deficit.
Items.title: ALDS Game 5
Items.vs: Cleveland Indians vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Addison Russell drove in four runs, Wade Davis earned a seven-out save, and the Chicago Cubs reached their third NL Championship Series in a row by edging the Washington Nationals 9-8 in a thriller of a Game 5.
Items.title: NLDS Game 5
Items.vs: Washington Nationals vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Dallas Keuchel dominated the Yankees again, striking out 10 in seven scoreless innings to lead the Houston Astros over New York 2-1 on Friday night in the AL Championship Series opener.
Items.title: ALCS Game 1
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Jose Altuve raced home on Carlos Correa's double in the ninth inning, Justin Verlander struck out 13 in a complete game and the Houston Astros beat the New York Yankees 2-1 Saturday for a 2-0 lead in the AL Championship Series.
Items.title: ALCS Game 2
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Chris Taylor hit a tiebreaking homer in the sixth inning, Yasiel Puig added a homer and an RBI double to his dynamite postseason and the Dodgers overcame a short start by Clayton Kershaw for a 5-2 victory over the Cubs in Saturday's NLCS opener.
Items.title: NLCS Game 1
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Justin Turner hit a three-run homer with two outs in the bottom of the ninth inning, and the Los Angeles Dodgers beat the Chicago Cubs 4-1 on Sunday to take a 2-0 lead in the NL Championship Series.
Items.title: NLCS Game 2
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Chicago Cubs

Items.description: Aaron Judge hit a three-run homer and a made pair of sparkling catches, leading CC Sabathia and the Yankees over the Houston Astros 8-1 Monday night and cutting New York's deficit to 2-1 in the best-of-seven AL Championship Series.
Items.title: ALCS Game 3
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Aaron Judge ignited a rousing rally with a home run, then doubled during a four-run eighth inning to spur the unflappable New York Yankees over the Houston Astros 6-4 Tuesday night and tie the AL Championship Series 2-2.
Items.title: ALCS Game 4
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Yu Darvish pitched into the seventh inning, Chris Taylor homered again and the Los Angeles Dodgers beat the Chicago Cubs 6-1 on Tuesday night to open a commanding 3-0 lead in the NL Championship Series.
Items.title: NLCS Game 3
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Masahiro Tanaka pitched seven innings of three-hit ball and the New York Yankees finally solved Houston Astros nemesis Dallas Keuchel, beating the ace lefty 5-0 on Wednesday for a 3-2 lead in the AL Championship Series.
Items.title: ALCS Game 5
Items.vs: New York Yankees vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: Javier Baez snapped an 0-for-20 skid with two home runs, Wade Davis hung on for a six-out save and the Chicago Cubs avoided a sweep, holding off the Los Angeles Dodgers 3-2 Wednesday night in Game 4 of the NL Championship Series.
Items.title: NLCS Game 4; 8pm ET if ALCS is over
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Kike Hernandez homered three times and drove in seven runs, and the Los Angeles Dodgers romped past the Chicago Cubs 11-1 on Thursday night behind Clayton Kershaw to reach the World Series for the first time in almost three decades.
Items.title: NLCS Game 5
Items.vs: Chicago Cubs vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Justin Verlander remained perfect with Houston, pitching seven shutout innings Friday night, and Jose Altuve homered and drove in three runs as the Astros extended the AL Championship Series to a decisive Game 7 with a 7-1 win over the New York Yankees.
Items.title: ALCS Game 6
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Charlie Morton and Lance McCullers combined for a three-hitter, Jose Altuve and Evan Gattis homered and the Houston Astros reached the World Series, blanking the New York Yankees 4-0 Saturday night in Game 7 of the AL Championship Series.
Items.title: ALCS Game 7
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. New York Yankees

Items.description: Clayton Kershaw strikes out 11 and Justin Turner delivers a tiebreaking, two-run homer as the Dodgers down the Astros 3-1 in Game 1 of the World Series.
Items.title: World Series Game 1
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: George Springer's two-run homer in the 11th inning gave the Houston Astros a 7-6 victory over the Los Angeles Dodgers in Game 2 of the World Series, evening the series at 1-1. There were eight home runs hit, six of them coming in the final three innings.
Items.title: World Series Game 2
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: A perfect fit in their own place, the Houston Astros are halfway home.
Items.title: World Series Game 3
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Cody Bellinger doubled and scored the tying run in the seventh inning, then doubled home the go-ahead run off closer Ken Giles in a five-run ninth inning that lifted Los Angeles to a 6-2 win Saturday night that tied the World Series at two games apiece.
Items.title: World Series Game 4
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Jose Altuve, Carlos Correa and the Astros kept hammering away in a wild slugfest that no one saw coming, rallying against Clayton Kershaw and rocking the Dodgers 13-12 in 10 thrilling innings Sunday night for a 3-2 lead in the World Series.
Items.title: World Series Game 5
Items.vs: Houston Astros vs. Los Angeles Dodgers

Items.description: Joc Pederson sliced a drive over the left-field wall, pounded his chest and danced around the bases, taking as many twists and turns as this World Series itself. Of course, the Los Angeles Dodgers forced the Houston Astros to Game 7.
Items.title: World Series Game 6
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Houston Astros

Items.description: From laughingstock to lift off.
Items.title: World Series Game 7
Items.vs: Los Angeles Dodgers vs. Houston Astros
